result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander John Enk was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Alexander John Enk is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Alexander John Enk was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing Hearing June 13, 2016
Reporter Jill Bartol

Defendant Alexander John Enk in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Alexander John Enk in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
All parties have received the PSI and are prepared to proceed today.  Counsel make sentencing arguments.  Defendant makes statement.
BY THE COURT:  Court sentences defendant to the Wisconsin Prison System for a period of 26 months:  14 months Initial Confinement followed by 12 months Extended Supervision, concurrent to Green Lake County cases 15CF127, 14CF95 & 15CF71.
 Conditions as follows:   *Granted 10 days credit for time already served.  *Maintain absolute sobriety.  *Not to be in possession of illegal drugs, drug paraphernalia, or prescription medications that do not belong to him.  *Shall not associate or affiliate with any known drug users/dealers or be in any establishment where drugs are being sold or used.   *Find and maintain full time employment.  *Shall not be in possession/control of any firearms.  *Provide DNA sample and pay $250.00 surcharge.  *Pay costs of $268.00 and any supervision fees as determined by the agent.  *Defendant is eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration program and the Substance Abuse program.  *Bond of $1,000.00 on file to be applied and any balance returned to the posted.
  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

Sentencing hearing on May 19, 2016 at 11:30 am.

Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.

  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 2.  Counts 1 & 3 to be dismissed.
Court orders a PSI.
Set for Sentencing
bond continued.

 **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

Defendant Alexander John Enk in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Alexander John Enk in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the matter is resolved today but in speaking with Atty Gumz; the defendant has not waived the Prelim and will be doing so today.  Atty Hendee states plea agreement and states that the parties will be asking for a PSI and a sentencing date.  Atty Gumz agrees and has discussed the waiver with his client.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees with the waiver.  Court accepts the waiver of the Prelim.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.

Atty Hendee states that the information is the same charges as in the criminal complaint and will be filing it shortly/.  Atty Gumz states that the defendant will proceed without that information filed right now.

Atty Hendee now files the information with the court and to the defense.  Atty Gumz received a copy of the information and agrees that it was the same charges.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 19, 2016 at 11:30 am.

Attorney Mark Jay Gumz in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Gumz states his client is in custody in Green Lake County.  Expects him to be there for some time.  Requests an additional return date in 60 days.
BY THE COURT:  Reset.  Bond continued.  Return date scheduled for March 17, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Alexander John Enk in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Alexander John Enk in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
 Atty Gumz states that the Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Atty Gumz states that the defendant will waive time limits for the Prelim.

BY THE COURT:  Time limits waived; set for return.
bond continued.

Atty Gumz states motion to modify the cash bail.  Atty Hendee responds and asks the court to deny the motion.
BY THE COURT:  Court denies the defendant's motion to modify the cash bail.  Return date scheduled for January 20, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
